CatDescriptText: William (Jack) Jackson, steward, Independent Club, 2166 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?" Answer reads: "Yes, I believe both parties have picked their best candidates in the past 10 years."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of William "Jack" Jackson wearing short sleeved check shirt, standing on sidewalk in front of building with glass block, possibly Centre Avenue
